New Posters Issued 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- New posters have been issued by the Central Art Studio.
 Among them is poster "We Will Follow the Leader to the End." Depicted on it are the shining star of marshal, colors of the three services of the Korean People's Army and red flags bearing words "Revolutionary spirit of Mt. Paektu", "Revolutionary soldier spirit," etc. on a ground showing ranks of demonstrators presenting letters " Unity in mind" with torches. It represents the fixed faith and will of the entire army and all the people to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They included posters "Let officials stand at the head of the ranks just as the commanding officers of the People's Army do!" "Let's fully display on all fronts the fighting spirit demonstrated in the 70s!" "Let's perform heroic feats in the building of hydro-power stations!" "Build more modern stock-breeding bases of our style!" and "Let's turn the whole country into a thick woodland and greenery!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also posters calling for voluntarily observing the revolutionary discipline concerning the labor administration and traffic rule and quitting smoking.

Sinister Scheme of Preemptive Attack on DPRK Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The test, production and deployment of missiles pertain to the legitimate, independent rights of the DPRK and no one is entitled to interfere in the issue as its missile development is entirely for self-defense, declares Rodong Sinmun Tuesday.
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is these days spreading the rumor that the DPRK is planning a missile test. This is nothing but an intentional and deliberate buildup of false rumor to keep the situation unstable on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK would not have bothered to manufacture missiles with so much trouble unless the U.S .resorted to military threat and aggressive war moves against it, having deployed a lot of nuclear weapons and missiles in and around south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is not in a position to talk about other's missile threat. It is none other than the U.S. which is producing and deploying the largest number of missiles on the globe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And it must not go unnoticed that the U.S. is openly scheming to mount a nuclear and missile preemptive strike at the DPRK. With "success" in the development of a super-high speed ground penetrating missile, it decided to transfer six of this type, first of all, to its forces in south Korea by the end of 2005. It has made a forward deployment of a squadron of F-15E fighter-bombers in south Korea allegedly to increase the capability of deployment in contingency on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists even brought into the East Sea of Korea Aegis destroyers equipped with a high-performance radar system and made them undertake operational duty under the excuse of coping with "the threat of north Korean ballistic missiles".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is freely setting afloat rumors about "north Korea's possible launching of ballistic missile" in an attempt to carry into practice its strategy of preemptive attack on the DPRK. The U.S. bellicose forces should abandon their impudent act to attain their criminal purpose by pulling up the  DPRK with sheer sophism.

Opening to Public of Negotiations on Transfer of U.S. Military�@Base Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity, the National People's Solidarity and six other organizations of south Korea reportedly called a press conference in Seoul on October 7 and demanded opening to the public of the truth behind the negotiations on the transfer of the U.S. military base from Ryongsan.
 The speakers at the press conference said the negotiations which proceeded according to the U.S. scenario would bring a greater disaster to the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said it would be conducive to peace and disarmament on the Korean peninsula to nullify the agreement on the transfer of the U.S. military base from Ryongsan. They demanded that the government open to the public the whole course of the negotiations and reexamine them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The open letter of protest read out at the press conference noted that the U.S. forced the signing of the agreement by all means available. It egged the pro-American flunkeyist ruling quarters to initial the agreement, the letter said, and added: This was, up to the hilt, an open challenge to the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded that the U.S. declare the negotiations totally null and void and stop the relocation of the U.S. forces threatening the peace and reunification of the Korean peninsula.

Deployment of Aegis Destroyers Condemned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Solidarity of Youth and Students for Implementing the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration reportedly made public a statement titled "We bitterly denounce deployment of U.S. Aegis destroyers in the East Sea" on October 6.
 Recalling the announcement of Secretary of the U.S. Navy Gordon England on October 1 that Aegis destroyers capable of chasing ballistic missiles had been deployed in the East Sea of Korea for the purpose of watching someone, the statement said this was aimed to ignite a war in the Korean peninsula at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We sternly denounce the U.S. deployment of Aegis destroyers in the East Sea of Korea and arms buildup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should attentively listen to the voices of all the people against war and the U.S. And it should immediately stop its arms buildup and leave this land with its forces and military hardware, the root cause of a war in the Korean peninsula. This is the only way out for the U.S.

Passage of "North Korean Human Rights Act" at U.S. Congress under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly made public a special statement on Oct. 7 as regards the U.S. extreme plot against the north.
 The statement noted that the passage of the "North Korean Human Rights Act" at the U.S. Congress is one more evidence proving that the U.S. scenario for a war against the north has entered the phase of its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is introducing ultra-modern weapons into the Korean peninsula under the pretext of redeploying U.S. forces abroad, while staging frantic nuclear war exercises against the north, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These facts clearly suggest that the "North Korean Human Rights Act" will be a prelude to the U.S. aggression against the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All members of the nation should unite as one and struggle for the repeal of the "Act" of the U.S., drive its troops, the root cause of war, out of south Korea to the last man and strangle the imperialists to death.

Anachronistic Folly of GNP Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for Abolition of the Security Law in south Korea reportedly held an urgent press conference in Seoul on Oct. 7.
 It issued a press release titled "We strongly denounce the Grand National Party, a conservative group of the Cold War era, for fostering anachronistic consciousness of crisis and disturbing society with a political coloring offensive." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press release said that the GNP in its "materials of the 2004 meeting of measures for the inspection of administration" launched again the hackneyed "coloring" offensive with a string of trash about "pro-north leftist forces" in a feverish attempt to foster the feeling of uneasiness among the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no ground for further existence of the GNP, which persistently negates reconciliation and peace between the south and the north and fans up confrontation and war crisis while twisting and turning in a desperate effort to defend the SL, the release said, and held that the evil law must be torn up under all circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the press conference the solidarity declared it would turn out in an all-out fight to frustrate the anti-national, anti-reunification and anti-human rights maneuvers of the GNP, the ultra right conservative group.

Pressure Will Not Work on DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The U.S.-led joint naval exercise is slated to be staged in the waters off Tokyo Bay of Japan in late October pursuant to the PSI aimed to stifle the DPRK.
 Commenting on this, Minju Joson Tuesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. -projected joint naval exercise brings into bolder relief the criminal nature of its moves against the DPRK. This only self-exposes that the U.S. attempt to form an international network of isolation and blockade against the DPRK and suffocate it remains unchanged and it is getting all the more pronounced. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The planned exercise is a wanton violation of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The DPRK is left with no option but to take necessary measures to defend its right to existence now that the U.S. scenario to stifle it at any cost has reached the phase of its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK cannot but take a serious view of the fact that Japan is zealously playing the role of a shock brigade in executing the U.S. policy for stifling it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Japan's participation in the U.S. coastal blockade against the DPRK is little short of jumping into fire with fagot on its back. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The DPRK will never remain a passive onlooker to the U.S. coastal blockade aimed to cut its lifeline but force U.S. to pay a high price for such act. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pressure will not work on the DPRK.

56th Anniversary of Opening of DPRK-Russia Diplomatic Ties�@Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Papers here Tuesday dedicate articles to the 56th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the DPRK and Russia.
 The opening of diplomatic ties between the two countries on October 12, 56 years ago was an event of weighty significance in the development of friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries, states Rodong Sinmun in its article. The author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The two countries have deepened their friendly bonds, closely cooperating with each other in different fields, political, economic, cultural, etc. on the principles of equality, independence and mutual benefit and now the DPRK-Russia friendly relations are developing in conformity with the desire and interests of the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the desire of the Russian people and the policy of the Russian government to build a powerful Russia and achieve national unity and social stability and development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now social and economic development is being made by the efforts of the Russian government and people. Deep concern is shown for the increase of the defense capabilities. Arms equipment of the Russian army is being modernized and its combat capability is growing. Work is in progress to wipe out the separatist gang and ensure social stability in Chechnya. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the international arena Russia rejects a unipolar world and seeks its multipolariation and is striving to ensure regional stability and global peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russia pays due attention to the improvement and development of relations with the countries of the commonwealth of independent states and European countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are interested in the affirmative developments in Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Minju Joson states that it is the common desire and demand of the two peoples to continue to develop the friendly relations between the two countries and the DPRK-Russia friendship will make a further favorable development by the joint efforts of the two peoples.

Aggressive Arms Buildup Must Be Stopped
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The United States is planning to send a Patriot Missile Unit to Kwangju, south Korea, soon in the wake of the deployment of its Aegis destroyers in the East Sea of Korea early this month.
  Viewing this as a proof of the promotion of the redeployment of the U.S. forces for invading the north in the last stage, a Minju Joson analyst Tuesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is as clear as noonday that in case the United States started a new war, a nuclear war, on the Korean peninsula, the Koreans in the north and the south would suffer the nuclear holocaust and the surrounding countries would not be able to evade the disaster. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will further increase the war deterrent in face of the prevailing situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a daydream for the United States to think of overwhelming the DPRK with arms as it did in Iraq and Afghanistan. The Korean army and people are fully prepared to destroy any aggressors at one blow. The aggressors pouncing upon us will never be able to go back alive. Then the south Korean bellicose elements who are set on confrontation with fellow countrymen in collusion with the U.S. will be meted out relentless punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States and the south Korean war-thirsty elements should cool their heads overheated with war fever and promptly stop the adventurous arms buildup against the north that would bring catastrophic consequences.

KCNA Refutes U.S. and Japan's Assertion about DPRK's "Missile�@Test"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The United States and Japan are asserting that the DPRK has a missile test-fire plan.
 Officials concerned of the governments and militaries of the two countries and their media raised a hue and cry over a threat from a new type medium-range ballistic missile, saying that north Korean army vehicles, soldiers and missile technicians are massed in the area around the launching base for missile Rodong and there is a sign of possible north Korean fire of a ballistic missile capable of striking the U.S. mainland and Japan proper. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The test, production and deployment of missiles are an issue pertaining to the legitimate right of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Therefore, the row kicked up by the U.S. and Japan over the DPRK's missiles can never work on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The test, production and deployment of missiles can never pose any threat to others as they are of self-defensive nature. The U.S. and Japan, however, are vociferous about the dangerous nature of the DPRK's missiles. This is related to their sinister political and military purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has increased its forces' capability to fight a war in Northeast Asia including the Korean peninsula and escalated their moves for military intervention under the pretext of "threat" from the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has massively shipped into areas around the DPRK its huge armed forces including nuclear-powered carrier in a bid to put the strategy of preemptive attack on it into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is according to this strategy that the U.S. has relocated its ground forces in south Korea and, at the same time, bolstered its naval and air forces there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is contemplating deploying a new carrier striking group in the Asia-Pacific region. It has already deployed its destroyers equipped with Aegis missile interceptor system in the East Sea of Korea and brought one squadron of air force F-15E to south Korea. All these military moves are part of its madcap arms buildup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has also shipped latest type tanks, armored vehicles, unmanned reconnaissance planes, Stealth fighter-bombers, missiles and other ultra-modern war means into south Korea according to its arms buildup plan in a bid to step up its preparations to stifle the DPRK by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has already worked out a detailed operational plan to fight a Korean war and, on this basis, intends to preempt an attack on the DPRK all of a sudden from the sea and air and on the land after transferring and amassing troops in operational theaters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These unprecedentedly reckless military moves on the part of the U.S. compel the army and people of the DPRK to harden their determination and will to exert utmost efforts to increase the defence capacity to defend the sovereignty of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand and mode of counteraction of the DPRK to keep itself fully ready for both dialogue and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will increase its military deterrent force in every way, now that the U.S. is becoming desperate in its moves to stifle it by force.

Natural Aroma Goods Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Natural aroma goods made by the Pyongyang Essential Oils Research Centre (e-mail:ksttc@co.chesin.com.) are popular among users.
 Chongsong (pine), Jinung (intellectual) and Wisaeng (hygienic) perfumes which are extracted from natural plants abundant in Korea provide clean environment and has a good effect on human body for their fresh and fragrant aroma. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongsong perfume extracted from needle-leaf trees including pine gives off fresh resin aroma. It removes mould and other unpleasant smell and provides aseptic environment in sauna. It makes people feel refreshed and protects bronchial tube. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jinung perfume emits such air smell as in deep forest or lake, thus creating a mild atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its ingredients are good for liver, stomach, lungs and other internal organs and have a strong germicidal power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also prevent aging by removing active oxygen in human body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They not only boost the contemplative and concentrative faculty of people but also relieve them from mental fatigue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wisaeng perfume has a strong insecticidal power. It is made with various aroma elements which give no harmful effect to human body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It prevents bedbug, mosquito and other insects from biting people. If people carry it with them inside or outside, it kills or expels insects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is good for the stability of blood pressure, pyretolysis, bronchitis and cold.

S. Korean Authorities Urged to Nullify Emergency Plan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- The south Korean authorities should disclose an "emergency plan to cope with the suddenly changed situation", declare it null and void and unconditionally apologize to the DPRK, holding responsibility for the grave impact the plan will have on the inter-Korean relations.
 A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland urged this in an answer given to a question put by KCNA Tuesday as regards the emergency plan allegedly to cope with the suddenly changed situation in the north, a very provocative plan which has been brought to light in south Korea recently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been disclosed that the south Korean authorities have steadily updated emergency plans such as Chungmu 3300 and Chungmu 9000, after working out them in secrecy in anticipation of what they call the suddenly changed situation in the north, the spokesman said, and continued: 
 It is the first time that the south Korean authorities are reported to have been watching for a chance after drafting a concrete plan to cope with the suddenly changed situation in the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent disclosure glaringly revealed that the authorities have sought a sinister aim while challenging the system in the north, pursuant to the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK behind the scene, although they have paid lip-service to reconciliation and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The CPRF considers this unpardonable act of the south Korean authorities against the north as a serious case quite contrary to the historic June 15 joint declaration and an extremely grave declaration of war against it and joins all the fellow countrymen in condemning it with surging resentment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are stunned by the behaviour of those talking about "suddenly changed situation" and "emergency plan" behind the scene with daggers in their belts while paying lip-service to "dialogue" and "cooperation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that the "Ministry of Unification" of south Korea has taken a direct part in updating the "emergency plan" aimed at confrontation with the north despite the fact that it has talked about "progress in inter-Korean relations" whenever an opportunity presented itself even after the publication of the June 15 joint declaration in which the north and the south committed themselves to achieve reconciliation, cooperation and independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We cannot but question whether Koreans do need "dialogue" and "cooperation" sought by those with such a sinister aim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for Korean-style socialism, it became several times stronger during the "Arduous March", undaunted by all challenges of imperialism, and it is now winning one victory after victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how desperately the anti-north fanatics in south Korea are working to do harm to the north, backed by outside forces, this will be nothing but a daydream. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will closely follow the attitude of the south Korean authorities and force them to pay dearly for their treacherous anti-reunification acts.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Air Force Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 12 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, inspected KPA Air Force Unit 2623.
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and Ri Yong Chol, member of the Central Military Commission of the WPK and first vice department director of its Central Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the unit's performance of the duty before looking round its combat and technical equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks for further increasing the combat capability of the unit, underscoring the need to pay primary attention to prizing and handling the weapons of the revolution associated with the people's blood and sweat like the apple of the eye. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round the room devoted to the history of the unit, guided by its commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the exploits performed by airmen, greatly pleased to learn that the unit has trained all of them into fighters fully prepared politically and ideologically and in military technique by waging a vigorous drive to implement the WPK's military line to the letter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round tall trees in the compound, he said it is necessary to put the work to create woodland and greenery on a scientific and technical basis under a long-term plan in order to spruce up the barracks like a park. He taught ways to do so one by one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at a flight training hall and met airmen in training. He acquainted himself in detail with their service ranging from their training to their dresses and had a warm conversation with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he took deep care of airmen's service and living, looking round a servicemen's hall, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a washroom, a daily provision store and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to learn that the unit has provided best conditions for servicemen's living and built modern entertainment and logistic facilities to suit the characteristic feature of the airmen, in particular. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underlined the need for the commanding officers to show special care for the airmen's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit.
